Groundfloor In The News



          "Closing the gap between the real estate investor and borrower through
          crowdfunding is what makes Groundfloor innovative"
          




          "“Developers ... have embraced the opportunity. They see it as a viable way to quickly raise cash for a project"
          







What Other Real Estate Investors Have to Say














Adam Ailion

              "My first GROUNDFLOOR project, which had 100% equity, was denied
              funding from a bank and a credit union since I owned the property
              for less than 6 months; I couldn’t even get a home equity line
              with my 740+ credit score! Thankfully Groundfloor arrived. The
              project funded relatively swiftly and the loan underwriting was
              timely and much smoother than what I’ve experienced at large
              banks. Loan servicing and post-closing support were also
              responsive and they were prompt to make payments on any
              construction draws."
              







Steve Brock

              "Groundfloor’s innovative approach to real estate financing is
              proving to be an effective way for us to keep pace with rising
              demand in our communities. I was blown away by how quickly and
              easily we were able to fund a project--it took less than 36 hours
              on our first deal."
              







John Mangham

              "We will defintely be using Groundfloor again. Groundfloor
              investors have become a meaningful part of our financing and
              business strategy. In addition to providing funds for our
              projects, we blieve that our cost of capital and fundraising
              timeline will decrease over time."
              










Is Your Project a Good Fit for Groundfloor?




            residential property: single-family or 1-4 unit.
          


            no owner-occupied, multi-family, land, new construction or blanket properties.
          


            loan between $50,000 - $250,000
          


            borrower operates under an active LLC or Corporation
          


            groundfloor will hold a senior lien position
          


            located in a state in which we actively lend
          


            principal's credit score is above 640
          









How Groundfloor Fix & Flip Loans Work


1 | APPLY


              Simple online loan application
            

              Complete at your convenience
            

              Get your rate in minutes
            




          Finance your next residential real estate project with Groundfloor.
          Applying for a loan is simple. Complete our online application and see
          your rate quote in just one click. Once your application is complete
          and submitted, our Lending Operations Team will connect with you to
          review your project and discuss details.
          








2 | FUND


              Thousands of investors funding loans
            

              Quick closing and access to funds
            

              No monthly payments
            




          Get funding fast. Once approved, we list your loan on our site and alert
          our community that a new loan is available for investment. Thousands of
          investors have the opportunity to fund your loan.
          

          When your loan is fully funded by Groundfloor investors, our Lending
          Operations Team will coordinate closing of the loan.
          









3 | FLIP


              Simple draw process for finished work
            

              Complete the renovation, sell the property
            

              Repay your Groundfloor loan
            




          Access funds efficiently. Submit draw requests throughout the life of
          the loan. Groundfloor wants your project to succeed and reimburses you
          for completed works using an efficient draw process.  Complete
          construction with no required monthly payments.  Without the burden
          of monthly interest payments you can focus on completing your project.
          














