                  JOB DESCRIPTION
                
Startup Strategy & Operations: Assist the Chief Executive Officer in planning for and closing additional rounds of capital sufficient to develop and grow the company. Play a key role within senior management team to formulate strategy and manage operations.
Financial Operations: Develop, manage and evolve appropriate processes and controls for transactions to and from retail investors and borrowers. Properly account for transactions related to the origination and repayment of real estate loans. At scale, the operation will consist of tens of thousands of monthly transfers and hundreds of real estate transactions in 50 to 100 localities nationwide. Solutions must be tax compliant and efficient for highly scalable business operations.
Regulatory Compliance: In collaboration with the Executive Vice President of Legal & Regulatory Affairs, ensure compliance with relevant federal and state securities laws. We are currently qualifying an umbrella offering under Regulation A as one step along a more extensive regulatory roadmap. Our offering circular already exceeds 350 pages, including fully audited financials.

                  PRODUCT
                
GROUNDFLOOR takes private lending public. We offer access for non-accredited and accredited investors to participate directly in short-term commercial construction loans backed by residential property, hyper-fractionalized to $10, at yields of 5-26%.
Even for accredited investors, high minimum requirements for capital and expertise conspire with securities regulations to block the vast majority of investors from participating in the lucrative market for private lending in real estate. Leveraging our proprietary underwriting engine and innovative application of existing securities law, we solve the hunt for yield for over 250 million non-accredited investors in the U.S.
We are the only "crowdfunding" platform in real estate that offers 100% of its loans for participation by all.

                  WHY US?
                
At GROUNDFLOOR, we believe that the broadest, most inclusive capital markets win -- for its participants and for society at large -- for the same reasons, functioning in the same way that the Internet itself does. While "crowdfunding for real estate" is a hot market, we stand alone as the only platform open to participation by all, including non-accredited investors. We view ourselves as creating a consumer product in finance with the same scale of impact and implications as the online discount brokerage industry had when it arose in the 1980s and 1990s.
Our team has succeeded before together, creating and launching Republic Wireless, a highly successful wireless company, in 2010-12. Our investor group is strong, and very committed. It's not too late to have a big impact on the culture we're building. Join us!

GROUNDFLOOR	Finance,	Inc. is	an	Equal	Opportunity	Employer	and	does	not	discriminate	against	any	employee	or	applicant	for	employment	because	of	race,	color, sex,	age,	national	origin,	religion,	sexual	orientation,	gender	identity	and/or	expression,	status	as	a	veteran,	and	basis	of	disability	or	any	other	federal,	state	or	local	protected class.                  







Devops Engineer 


Submit Resumé




GROUNDFLOOR is an Atlanta­based fintech startup opening the market for peer­to­peer lending in real estate. We're looking for an accomplished devops engineer to identify, troubleshoot and resolve software and service issues. The ideal candidate is motivated by the opportunity to build a distinctive brand, product and service that stands apart in a field of many that aim to reformat banking, finance and investing. As a company, we value and select for intellect, strategic thinking, authenticity and integrity.

Requirements:

3+ years experience in Systems Engineering/DevOps role.
1+ year of ruby (Other OO languages will be considered). 
You function well in a fast-paced, informal environment where constant change is the norm and the bar for quality is set high.
You have a technical background and a BS or MS in a computer-related or hard science field.

Communication:

You communicate clearly and efficiently in verbal and written communication both inside and outside of the team.

Technical Skills:

Understand that programming languages are tools, not ideologies and are comfortable working in the right one for the task at hand (we use Ruby on Rails).
Demonstrated ability to work with SQL and databases.
Experience with highly available and high-performance open source web technologies.
Experience troubleshooting problems and working with a team to resolve large scale production issues.

Bonus Points:

You feel comfortable doing things, even when no one is telling you exactly what to do.
The idea of owning our back office.
You are not wedded to any particular development philosophy or buzzword; instead you believe in adapting your skills to the needs and personalities on a team as it grows.
You know and love Postgres.
Rails and activeadmin are great tools that you love to use.

Here's how we interview:
You will have a quick (30min or less) video or phone call to kick off the process.  You will be asked some general questions about your development history and style. Of course you will have plenty of opportunity to ask us anything that might be on your mind. 
If things go well we will ask you to do some work on a very small sample project.  Fork a github repo, fix a couple of bugs and add any additional items that you want to show us how you typically work.   We expect this exercise to take a couple of hours at most.   This is meant to give us a small sense what you do and how you do it.  
Finally if things are still looking good you will be asked to join us for a team lunch and then spend the afternoon reviewing your project, talking about work and getting to know the team a little more.

GROUNDFLOOR is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.





