Manager, Loan Originations 


Submit Resumé





                  Are you interested in joining a startup and helping it reach the next stage of growth? Are you a proven real estate professional with a successful track record of lending, particularly in the private money arena for commercial loans on residential real estate?
                

                  GROUNDFLOOR is an Atlanta­based fintech startup opening the market for peer­to-peer lending in real estate. We're expanding our Lending Operations team, responsible for scaling best practices and efficiencies to create the best possible customer experience for our borrowers.
                
What You'll Do

Become an expert at using lead generation tools to routinely extract contacts and create accurate and targeted lists of prospects.
Conduct sales development best practices with email, phone, and social drips to connect with new prospects.
Manage the collection and organization of all elements of the loan package and coordinate submission to Loan Committee.
Find, administer, help develop and optimize the tools and services utilized by GROUNDFLOOR's sales and operations organizations as we begin to scale nationally.


What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree
Strong written communication, phone, presentation, and interpersonal skills.
Hustle and persistence
Must be comfortable and effective with top of the funnel objections, prospecting, cold calling, online, as well as have excellent interpersonal & technical skills.
Highly organized and strong time management skills.
Contagious passion and empathy for the customer, but the tenacity to get them through the sales funnel efficiently.
Experience collaborating and planning with tools such as Salesforce, Desk.com, Slack and the like.
While we are not a traditional real estate lender, experience with residential real estate is highly desired.
Experience working on a fast­ paced, highly ­visible team; your work will have serious impact here.
Balance attention to detail with swift execution  we need to do things quickly, and we need to do them well.
Balancing those can be challenging, and this should be a strength.
Experience with standard residential real estate laws and real estate loan closings will be a significant advantage.
Desire to grow and learn new things every day.
Ability to work in fast paced, changing environment with minimal direction.


Bottom Line
You have to be ready to hustle! We move fast...done is better than perfect, and continual iteration is important. You must be ready and excited to learn on your feet and help build a growing business. This position is based in Atlanta.


