×



Brian Dally
Co-Founder & CEO
brian@groundfloor.us








Brian is a co-founder and director of GROUNDFLOOR and serves as our CEO. He is responsible for marketing as well as setting long term direction and goals for the company.
Brian's 15 year career building disruptive technology startups spans stints in Silicon Valley, Boston, London and the North Carolina Triangle region. Previously, he led the launch of Republic Wireless to take on the big four cellphone carriers to international acclaim. As a result, millions more Americans can now afford a smartphone.
Brian has a JD from Harvard Law School, an MBA from Harvard Business School, and a BA with Highest Distinction from the University of Virginia.













×



Nick Bhargava
Co-Founder & EVP Regulatory Affairs
nick@groundfloor.us








Nick is a co-founder and director of GROUNDFLOOR and EVP Regulatory Affairs. He leads product development and is responsible for regulatory strategy.
An expert in securities law, Nick was heavily involved in the JOBS Act as an early pioneer who advanced the concept of crowdfunding. Nick and Brian met through Groundwork Labs in the Triangle-area startup hub the American Underground. His years in finance have included work for the Financial Services Roundtable, SEC, FINRA, TD Waterhouse and RBC Financial Group.
Nick received his LLM at Duke University School of Law and holds a BS in Biological Sciences and Business from the University of Alberta.













×



Chris Schmitt
VP Software
chris@groundfloor.us








Chris writes code. Lots of it, quickly. And it works. He drives software development and technology for GROUNDFLOOR.
Chris is a full stack developer with over 15 years of software experience, including stints working in the trenches with Brian and Ben at Republic Wireless and building financial services backend systems for Fidelity. He loves agile development practices and lean startup principles. On the weekends he enjoys hanging out with his two sons or spending the afternoon flying.
Chris earned his BA from Roger Williams University.













×



Matthew May
Chief Financial Officer
matthew@groundfloor.us








Matthew is the Chief Financial Officer of GROUNDFLOOR. He is responsible for SEC compliance and overseeing our back office finance and accounting functions.
Matthew’s 20 year career in Austin and Atlanta has centered around guiding technologies through high growth. Previously, he was an audit partner with the 25th largest accounting firm in the US.
Matthew is a certified public accountant in Georgia and Texas and has a BBA in Accounting from Baylor University.













×



Dee Dee Stevens
Manager, Employee Relations
deedee@groundfloor.us








Dee Dee is our Employee Relations Manager. She manages the day to day employee needs as well as all the internal workings of the office while also assisting the Marketing VP and Brian to schedule and implement events and community outreach for GROUNDFLOOR.
Dee Dee has worked in several office administration roles and brings organizational and planning skills to the team while providing executive assistance as needed. She enjoys creative projects and celebrates company wins by providing cupcakes to the team.
Dee Dee earned her BS from the University of Alabama.













×



Hunter Stewart
Engineer
hunter@groundfloor.us



Hunter is an engineer at GROUNDFLOOR where he works on everything from developing new features to back-office systems. He loves building web applications and writing Ruby code. When he's not coding, you can find Hunter running, recording music, or at a taco truck.
Hunter graduated summa cum laude with a B.A. in Philosophy from Belhaven University where he focused on logic and Aristotelian metaphysics.













×



Anthony Byram
Senior Engineer
anthony@groundfloor.us



Anthony is a Senior Software Engineer at GROUNDFLOOR. He started programming in 8th grade and hasn't stopped since. He started his career by joining a startup as CTO where he managed technology for six years. From there, he joined another startup in the same role. With eight years of full stack web application engineering experience and technical leadership, he brings a wealth of technical knowledge to the team. He is now enjoying his role as Senior Software Developer while mastering the skills that matter most to him.
Outside of work, Anthony enjoys playing board games with his wife and children, Olympic weight lifting, cycling, and being outdoors.
Anthony studied Mathematics at the University of Michigan Ann Arbor.













×



Glenn Gilbert
Director of Asset Management
glenn@groundfloor.us








Glenn serves as our Director of Asset Management. Glenn is a construction and finance attorney from Australia who relocated to the United States in July 2012 and to assist with the establishment of a US based property company that primarily specialized in the acquisition, renovation and sale of US single family homes to investors in Australia and Asia.
During his time in the States, Glenn has been involved in over 120 property flips and brings his experience as a developer, contractor and owner to the Groundfloor asset management team to focus on borrower success throughout the loan life cycle.
Glenn graduated from Bond University in 2003 with a Bachelor of Commerce (Finance Major) and a Bachelor of Laws.  Glenn was a sitting member of the Law Institute of Victoria Property Dispute Resolution Committee throughout 2012.













×



Andrew Mandel
Systems Analyst
mandel@groundfloor.us








Andrew is the Systems Analyst here at Groundfloor. With a technical focus on the operations of the business, he will assist the Development team with optimizing and automating the customer experience - from onboarding to investing, as well as enhancing the lending operations.
Andrew comes to us from BitPay where he served as the Enterprise Relationship Manager on the Client Operations team. Prior to BitPay, he was a Technical Business Analyst with CoStar Real Estate Manager.
Andrew received his BBA in Management Information Systems from the Terry School of Business at the University of Georgia. Go Dawgs!













×



Patrick Donoghue
Director of Lending Operations




Patrick Donoghue has served as Director of Lending Operations for Groundfloor since January 2016. Prior to this Patrick served as Senior Associate for RevitaLending where he worked to optimize the firm’s capital market structure and proliferate the loan growth model. As VP of Wholesale Operations for ACC Mortgage Patrick managed the entire loan process for a significant broker channel reviewing and funding private money loan transactions.
Patrick has been active in the private lending space since 2006 underwriting, originating and servicing private money loans. Prior to this Patrick served as production manager and originator for various mortgage companies and began his career as a Branch Manager for the United States Senate FCU. As Director of Lending Operations Patrick is helping refine Groundfloor’s lending policy and practices. Heading the underwriting of all loans and managing the real estate closing process.
Patrick graduated from Edinboro University of Pennsylvania with a B.A. in Psychology in 1997













×



Justin Burris
Senior Engineer
justin@groundfloor.us








Justin is a Senior Software Engineer at Groundfloor. He has a history delivering well tested, robust web applications which solve real world problems for customers. His goal is to make sure the team is able to deliver high quality work at a strong pace.
Based out of Atlanta, Justin has worked at small startups to companies in the Fortune 100. His job has taken him around the world, where he worked on a project for the Singaporean government.
Justin loves whitewater kayaking, board games, and spending his time working on projects to make his home much smarter than he is.
Justin graduated with a BS in Computer Science from Georgia Southern University.













×



Rich Pulido
SVP, Head of Lending and Risk Management
rich@groundfloor.us








Rich is the Senior Vice President of Real Estate Operations. He is responsible for designing and building systems and processes critical to the origination, underwriting, closing, and servicing of commercial loan assets. Rich's scope spans individual loans to the entire portfolio. He strives to ensure Groundfloor's investors and borrowers have positive user experiences supported by industry leading risk management practices.
Rich comes to Groundfloor after a 27-year commercial real estate career with Prudential. His broad experience base includes equity and debt asset management, development, portfolio management and capital market assignments.  Significantly, during the Great Recession, Rich led the Special Servicing team responsible for loan workouts and REO for a $55 billion portfolio of commercial mortgages. He also started a capital markets unit, building up a $1 billion book. Rich's experience is national in scope during his career Rich has worked in Chicago, Los Angeles, and Atlanta.
After earning a BS in System Science and Mathematics from UCLA, Rich was a Systems Engineer with Northrop Corp.  working on classified military aircraft projects. He subsequently earned his MBA from The University of Chicago Booth School of Business.













×



Angela Ellison
Lending Operations Manager
angela@groundfloor.us








Angela Ellison manages works with our borrowers to ensure a smooth process from app submission to loan closing.
Angela has a broad background in operations spanning a number of different industries.













×



Matt Campbell
Director, Business Development
matt@groundfloor.us








Matt Campbell leads loan sales at Groundfloor.
With over 20 years in the mortgage industry, Matt is a key component of our Borrowers' success.













×



Cary Eisenberg
Account Management Director
cary@groundfloor.us








Cary serves as an Account Management Director. He is a 3rd generation Atlantan. After an early career as Merchandise Manager for a number of Rock and Roll bands. Cary joined American Home Mortgage in 1992 focused primarily on consulting and financing of owner -occupied single family residences.
He found a wonderful opportunity to join Groundfloor in September 2016 to use his extensive industry knowledge to further Groundfloor's business.













×



Clayton Putala
Portfolio Analyst
clayton@groundfloor.us



Clayton serves as our Portfolio Analyst.  He works with our SVP of Lending and Risk Management to track portfolio performance, risk management and capital planning. He also works with the Director of Asset Management on loan servicing and tracking all active loans from closing to repayment.
Clayton joins us from Blackbaud in Charleston, SC where he worked in Finance and IT Asset Management.
Clayton earned is BS from The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina and subsequently earned his MBA from The Citadel Graduate College.













×



David Ellenburg
Sales Development Representative
david@groundfloor.us



David Ellenburg is a Senior Sales Development Representative at Groundfloor. He works with our borrowers and investors to help them be successful and to reach their goals.
David has over 25 years of Mortgage Banking, Business Banking and Risk Management experience. He has worked for PNC, Regions, Fifth Third, and United Community Bank. He has also been active in the Nonprofit arena helping families achieve their dream of homeownership and also in the Profit arena helping families achieve their dream of homeownership.













×



Deborah Johns
Senior Loan Processor
dj@groundfloor.us



Deborah Johns is our Senior Loan Processor. She processes your loans from application to final approval.
Deborah will be your point of contact throughout your loan process.
Deborah, has worked in all facets of the mortgage banking & real estate industry and brings a professional "can do" attitude with extensive mortgage banking & real estate skills to the team.













×



Marge Smith
Closer
marge@groundfloor.us



Marge Smith serves as our Closer in the Loan department. She ads unparalleled value to our team with her years of experience.
Marge has been in the lending closer business since 1980. Experience has been with the title side as well as major lenders.
Marge graduate of University of Minnesota in business, and Kennesaw state Certified paralegal.













×



Andy DeVane
Engineer
andy@groundfloor.us



Andy is a Software Engineer at Groundfloor. Andy has a background in many creative fields such as video production, motion animation,graphic design, and more. He began his development career in 2014 by learning the Ruby programming language.
Before Groundfloor, he worked with small businesses, non-profits, and startups developing web applications.
Andy was previously a Full Stack Developer at Agency Spotter where he was responsible for building out features from the ground up.













×



Benjamin Sutton
Controller and Director of Finance
sutton@groundfloor.us



Benjamin is our Controller and Director of Finance of GROUNDFLOOR. He is responsible for the day to day finance and accounting functions.
Benjamin's career began in the Audit practice at KPMG LLP. He then worked in a financial reporting role at a public company during the company’s initial public offering.
Benjamin is a certified public accountant in Georgia and Virginia and has a MAcc from the University of North Florida and BS in Accounting from the University of Florida.













×



Michelle Garrison
Head of Investor Care
michelle@groundfloor.us



Michelle is the Head of Investor Care at GROUNDFLOOR and her role is to develop and guide our Investor Services department.  This role was added as acknowledgement of the importance of our unique investor community and their service needs.
Her background includes 30 years of experience designing, honing and leading customer care organizations in cultures demanding extraordinary service.  Her strong background is complimented by a passion for facilitating service to others.
Engineering and artistic genes run deep in Michelle’s family tree and she claims to have received both.  She uses them to develop processes and experiences that surprise,delight and satisfy our investors.  Her goal is to assure that each investor service interaction is a positive, memorable experience.













×



Jeff Seal
Director of Account Management
jeff@groundfloor.us



Jeff is a Director of Account Management and has over 11 years’ experience in the finance and default servicing industries collectively. Previously, Jeff spent 7 years working for a number of national real estate auction platforms and served as their Vice President of Product and Client Management. He managed the daily communication with high level clients as well as developed new business products for the platform nationally.
Prior to joining the GroundFloor team, Jeff was the Director of Business Development for a national private equity owned firm focused on investor financing across 46 states. Jeff led the formation of the short term financing products and was responsible for creating the underwriting and process flows for related products. Jeff is an avid competitor in the cycling and running community with 25 years of competitive activity. In his spare time he sits on multiple boards within his community with respect to ministry efforts across the world as well as a local focus specific to men’s ministry.













×



Rodney Fowlkes
Engineer
rodney@groundfloor.us



Rodney is a Software Engineer at Groundfloor. As a front-end developer, he is responsible for the UX/UI design and development on the Groundfloor platform. With a creative background, Rodney got into javascript development to fulfill a longtime passion for problem solving.
Before Groundfloor Rodney spent time consulting and working at an interface development agency gaining experience collaborating on scalable enterprise software.













